The Senate developed its proposal through a working group rather than the commiltee system. S. 2852 was introduced on October 3. On October 14, the Senate passed H.R. 5210, with amendments, in lieu of S. 2852, and sent their message to the House on October 18.
Differences between the two versions were worked out through a series of informal negotiations, rather than a formal conference. Meetings of House and Senate staff were held to work out differences. Where staff could not reach agreement, matters were referred to members. In some cases, for example the provisions creating the "drug czar," provisions debated and passed by each house were very different and the final compromise differed from these proposals.

